New Records: Jett Howard scored a career-high 21 points
Key Match Events: Brice Sensabaugh hit two 3-pointers and scored eight straight Utah points early in the fourth quarter, stretching an 11-point lead to 17
Pre-Game Insights: The Jazz played without most of their starting lineup due to injuries and did not play Lauri Markkanen, John Collins and Keyonte George.
The Magic played without their top four scorers due to injuries, including Jalen Suggs, Paolo Banchero, Franz Wagner and Mo Wagner.
Post-Match Reflections: The Jazz won two games in a row, including this 105-92 victory over the Magic.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Jazz are 6-4 against Eastern Conference competition, and 3-21 against the West.
Seven of their nine wins have come on the road.
Others: The Magic shot 36% overall and made 14 of 47 3-point shots (30%).
Wendell Carter Jr. had 15 points and Cole Anthony added 12 points in his first start since the final game of the 2022-23 season.
